text:
East 3rd Street, south side, east from and including Lewis, to, but not including Tompkins Streets.
September 16, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.

The New York Times (May, 1938) reports the demolition of No. 386 East 3rd Street (3 story, white front building), a structure four doors from the S.E. corner of Lewis Street.
